item.title: Getting some cash ;)
item.dc:creator: @Iamadam Iamadam
item.description:
@Iamadam wrote:

^^ Oh really, Never figured that one out

Thanks for the help people.[quote=“tehubernoobers, post:10, topic:8533”]let me say that you should just stick to runecrafting natures through the abyss, first you catch enough lobbys as you will need alot of food to runecraft… seeing as you get attacked every time in abyss by abyssal monsters and rc pkers also. anyways you need many glory ammys to teleport to edgeville and restock on pure ess, i recommend you get 5 - 6 glorys. also be sure to collect pouches from abyss monsters to as that will help you runecraft more ess and help you in the long run i suppose. also make sure you take with you 1 law and 5 airs as you will need these to teleport away if you are snared or frozen by pkers or are just in trouble. if you runecraft 10k pure ess which is 1 mil or you can mine it yourself, you can easily get 3 - 4 mil from making it into nats, natures normally sell for 300 - 350 gp. then after that buy 40k more pure ess with the money you have and then you can get 12 - 14 mil if done right. you can keep buying more pure ess and making more money by doing this… i suggest that after you get around 30 - 50 mil buy santa hats and merchant them to make good money. good day [/quote]
Ya, I got 71 rc on my old account. I never took food though the abyss though - waste of space. Also, instead of runes, bring an ectophial

item.title: Getting some cash ;)
item.dc:creator: @Pee_Hat Pee Hat
item.description:
@Pee_Hat wrote:

Those arent bad stats , but i wouldn’t suggest using your skills to make money just yet. Try the most noobish accurate way of making money which is picking white berries in the elven forest. You must have done mourning ends 1 or atleats started it tot he part where u can use the latya bank (hope i spelled it right) kill the elves there get alot of tele crystal chagre them and use them to tele back to bank when u have full invent of them. If ur not sure where they are look in Runehq map. (They sell for 900-1k ea fast on forums)

Also if you wanna try a more non boring way first start crafting nats its a very nice way of making a nice 2m a day. I hope u already have some backgorund info on how to make nats.

Then after you have made some decent money such as 1.5-3m , invest it in barrow equipment and by that i mean the recomnded items needed to do reapted barrow trips.

Also you could invest some of your money into your skills and let those skills make the money back, RC is probably the best skill u can invest on, then u can also do fletching , smithing (takes too long) , herblore (expensive not recomended for broke newbs) , and farming, herb seeds is a very nice way too i did i for quite some time.

Hope it helped , i’ll try to think of more ways.

~ Pee Hat ~
